npm init
npm i express
npm i nodemon
    nodemon app.js (continuous run/refresh)
** new cmd **
npm i -g pm2
    pm2 start app.js (start pm2)
download stable version Nginx: https://nginx.org/en/download.html    
    extract into c:/program files
    change .conf file 



notes:
pm2 aids in reverse proxy 

PM2: 'a production process amnager for Node.js apps that has a built-in load balancer. It allows you to keep
    apps running forever, reloads them without downtime, helps to amnage app logging, monitoring, and clustering.'
        - expressjs.com 